'...you are a professor I understand. Well, Professor, from now on a great future lies before you. We must now educate the ignorant, the moody, the wicked — but educate them in a new way. Just think of all the trash we used to be taught... Think of the millions of unnecessary books accumulating in libraries. The books they print! You know — you will never believe me — but I have been told by a reliable person that in one bookshop there actually is a book of